senses
  entry
    definition "an instance of questioning"
    examples ("there was a question about my training" "we made inquiries of all those who were present")
    id oewn-07208256-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (inquiry enquiry query interrogation)
  entry
    definition "the subject matter at issue"
    examples ("the question of disease merits serious discussion" "under the head of minor Roman poets")
    id oewn-06796625-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (head)
  entry
    definition "a sentence of inquiry that asks for a reply"
    examples ("he asked a direct question" "he had trouble phrasing his interrogations")
    id oewn-07211342-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (interrogation interrogative "interrogative sentence")
  entry
    definition "uncertainty about the truth or factuality or existence of something"
    examples ("the dubiousness of his claim" "there is no question about the validity of the enterprise")
    id oewn-04764777-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (doubt dubiousness doubtfulness)
  entry
    definition "a formal proposal for action made to a deliberative assembly for discussion and vote"
    examples ("he made a motion to adjourn" "she called for the question")
    id oewn-07178244-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (motion)
  entry
    definition "an informal reference to a marriage proposal"
    examples ("he was ready to pop the question")
    id oewn-07176710-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "challenge the accuracy, probity, or propriety of"
    examples ("We must question your judgment in this matter")
    id oewn-00869073-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (oppugn "call into question")
  entry
    definition "pose a series of questions to"
    examples ("The suspect was questioned by the police" "We questioned the survivor about the details of the explosion")
    id oewn-00789846-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (interrogate)
  entry
    definition "pose a question"
    id oewn-00786670-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (query)
  entry
    definition "conduct an interview in television, newspaper, and radio reporting"
    id oewn-00810517-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (interview)
  entry
    definition "place in doubt or express doubtful speculation"
    examples ("I wonder whether this was the right thing to do" "she wondered whether it would snow tonight")
    id oewn-00927081-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (wonder)
